# Support query → Markdown (Launch_queries knowledge base)

When the user provides a **raw support conversation** (paste, export, or thread) and wants a **Markdown file** saved in this repo (or refined), treat that as authoring a **lasting KB entry**. Do **not** mirror the transcript as a diary.

## Remove (noise)

Greetings/closings, scheduling (“DM me”, “sending invite”), thanks-only lines, pings and CC lists, Slack deep links unless they encode unique technical facts, filler (“any luck?”), duplicate restatements of the same point, emoji-only replies, empty “checking this” updates **unless** they add a new finding.

Keep thread order only **where** it resolves ambiguity (e.g. correction then resolution).

## Preserve (signal)

**QUESTION territory:** Stable facts—product (Launch, Edge, OAuth, Next.js-on-Launch, etc.), environment, **symptoms**, reproduction, **URLs/paths/query params**, **HTTP status codes**, timing (Sudden vs after deploy), comparative behavior (production vs local), hypotheses the customer stated.

**ANSWER territory:** Confirmed diagnoses, investigations (what was ruled in/out), **platform-side explanation**, **customer/app-side observations**, known **framework quirks** if mentioned (e.g. Next.js redirects), **workarounds**, config/env checks suggested, ownership (“we’re investigating”), and **resolution status** when stated (resolved, mitigated, open).

If no solid answer exists in the thread, write **ANSWER** as investigation status + verified facts + suggested next checks—do **not** invent conclusions.

## Redact

Replace secrets and high-cardinality IDs with placeholders: tokens, `state`/`code`/`client_secret`-like values—use **`xxxx`** or **`<redacted>`**; shorten long stack traces to one representative line unless every line differs meaningfully.

## Output shape

Use **exactly two top-level headings** so files stay consistent:

```markdown
QUESTION

<One or two concise paragraphs: problem, scope, facts. No narrator voice.>

ANSWER

<Structured body. Prefer short sections with Markdown **bold** on key terms, bullets for lists.>

```

Optional **ANSWER** subsections (use only what the thread supports), e.g.: **Symptoms**, **Investigation**, **Cause / hypotheses**, **Workarounds**, **Suggested checks**, **Framework / app notes**, **Resolution**.

Match tone and density of existing entries in this folder (professional, runnable as internal KB).

## File naming & location

Save as **`kebab-case-topic.md`** inside the **feature folder** that best matches the query (not repo root). Current folders, by Launch feature area:

- **`custom-domains-ssl/`** — custom domains, apex/A records, DCV, SSL/TLS certs, branded domains
- **`edge-functions-rewrites/`** — Edge Functions, Edge URL Rewrites / `launch.json`
- **`deployments-builds/`** — deployments, build machines, build/install failures, runtime cache
- **`caching-cdn/`** — CDN caching, cache invalidation/revalidation, origin traffic, personalization
- **`logs-monitoring/`** — Log Targets / log volume, OpenTelemetry, uptime/site monitoring
- **`networking-connectivity/`** — egress/outbound IPs, allowlisting, connectivity errors (CF1003, 520), OAuth/network
- **`integrations/`** — Git/GitHub connections, Marketplace apps, third-party integrations

If the query spans areas, pick the **primary feature** and cross-link related entries with `@path`. If none fit, create a **new feature folder** (kebab-case) rather than dumping at root. If the topic already exists, **update that file** or ask whether to supersede vs archive.

**Always update `README.md`** when adding, renaming, or removing an entry: add/edit a one-line index entry under the correct folder heading — `[Title](folder/file.md) — symptom→answer hook. _Keywords: ..._`. The README is the retrieval map; keep it in sync.

## When the paste is ambiguous

Prefer **labeled uncertainty** (“not confirmed in thread”) over guessing. If critical technical fields are missing, list them as **Suggested checks** rather than asserting.
